{
  "card_id": "new_york_manipulation_profile",
  "type": "merged_concept",
  "canonical_term": "New York Manipulation Profile",
  "aliases": [
    "New York Manipulation",
    "new york manipulation",
    "NY Manipulation",
    "ny manipulation",
    "NY Manipulation Daily Profile",
    "ny manipulation daily profile"
  ],
  "school": "ICT",
  "definition": "A daily profile where London consolidates or fails to reach a higher time frame PD array, then the New York AM session manipulates the London range via a liquidity sweep, triggering a Change in the State of Delivery (CHoCH/MSS) on the 5-minute chart, followed by a strong directional move to the true target. Expresses the Power of Three: Accumulation (London), Manipulation (NY sweep), Distribution (NY directional delivery).",
  "identification_rules": [
    "During the London Kill Zone (02:00–05:00 EST), price consolidates or fails to take out a significant swing high or low, leaving the range largely intact.",
    "At 08:30 or 09:30 EST, price sweeps liquidity on one side of the London range (or a nearby swing) in the direction opposite to the anticipated true move.",
    "After the manipulation sweep, a Change in the State of Delivery (CHoCH/MSS) is confirmed on the 5-minute chart by a close beyond a series of same-direction candles in the reversal direction.",
    "The daily candle structure resolves as Open-High-Low-Close (bearish) or Open-Low-High-Close (bullish), with the manipulation forming the wick and distribution forming the body.",
    "The true directional move (distribution) targets an external liquidity level such as Previous Day High/Low or a higher-time-frame PD array identified on the daily chart.",
    "Ensure the sweep is in the opposite direction of intended order flow / daily bias.",
    "Validate the structure maps to an Open-Low-High-Close (bullish) or Open-High-Low-Close (bearish) Power of Three on the daily or 4-hour candle."
  ],
  "trading_implication": "Traders wait for London to consolidate without reaching a key HTF level, then monitor 08:30 and 09:30 EST for a manipulation sweep. Entry is taken after a confirmed Change in the State of Delivery on the 5-minute chart, ideally at a discount (for longs) or premium (for shorts) within the range, such as an order block or fair value gap. Stop is placed beyond the manipulation extreme; target is the opposing external liquidity (e.g., Previous Day High/Low). Standard deviation projections (2–2.5 and 4–4.5) can confirm expansion targets.",
  "common_mistakes": [
    "Entering in the direction of the manipulation sweep rather than waiting for the Change in the State of Delivery to confirm the true directional move.",
    "Using the daily open price as an entry instead of waiting for price to retrace to a discount (for longs) or premium (for shorts) within the range after the CHoCH.",
    "Failing to confirm the CHoCH on the lower time frame (5-minute) before entering, leading to premature entries against the manipulation move.",
    "Confusing this profile with a London Reversal or New York Reversal by not verifying that London genuinely consolidated rather than making a significant directional move.",
    "Anticipating the profile when London has already reached the higher time frame key level, eliminating the need for New York manipulation."
  ],
